<h1>Overnight Oats</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1 1/2 cup rolled oats</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon chia seeds</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon flaxseed meal</li>
  <li>10 dried goji berries</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Add all ingredients to a 1-pint mason jar.</li>
  <li>Add water to jar until there is only about 1/4 inch of space left at the top.</li>
  <li>Close the lid.</li>
  <li>Shake vigorously for five seconds.</li>
  <li>Place in the fridge overnight.</li>
  <li>Eat the next day (or up to a week later) with sliced banana, chopped strawberries, frozen blueberries, and/or any combination of fruits on hand.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Before putting overnight oats into serving bowl, place a few tablespoons of Grape-Nuts in bowl. Don't mix Grape-Nuts into the oats, instead wait until you've eaten most of the oats.</li>
  <li>Add 1/4 cup oat milk after you've added Grape-Nuts, oats, and fruit.</li>
</ul>
